d%20community%20are%20ways%20to%20get%20started%20and%20monetize%20what%20you%20already%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20interesting%20thing%20about%20a%20portfolio%20career%20is%20that%20there%20are%20an%20infinite%20number%20of%20ways%20that%20it%20can%20be%20structured%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20really%20depends%20on%20the%20individual%2C%20what%20they're%20hoping%20to%20achieve%2C%20how%20much%20stability%20they%20want%2C%20what%20their%20risk%20appetite%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Mackenzie%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuilding%20a%20portfolio%20of%20different%20kinds%20of%20gigs%20could%20take%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20unlikely%20that%20you'll%20set%20off%20on%20your%20portfolio%20career%20and%20add%20another%20job%20to%20your%20portfolio%20as%20a%20freelancer%20or%20a%20consultant%20and%20then%20you'll%20land%20another%20gig%20in%20two%20days%20after%20announcing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Abrahami%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20goes%20through%20a%20process%2C%20and%20it%20often%20takes%20a%20lot%20longer%20than%20you%20would%20expect%2C%20so%20you%20need%20to%20have%20a%20comfortable%20financial%20runway%20to%20see%20you%20through%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20planning%20to%20build%20a%20portfolio%20career%20without%20having%20a%20full-time%20job%2C%20networking%20could%20be%20helpful%20before%20quitting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBuilding%20your%20network%20is%20something%20that%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Mackenzie%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3Breally%20expanding%20the%20network%20and%20making%20really%20good%20connections%20and%20building%20relationships%20within%20their%20sphere%20or%20within%20their%20space%20is%20something%20that%20you%20can%20do%20while%20you%20have%20a%20full-time%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3a1c082-079e-4ce6-9814-b1f84e3b11bd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20a%20portfolio%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMackenzie%20and%20Abrahami%20both%20think%20a%20portfolio%20career%20isn't%20for%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20person%20who%20would%20thrive%20with%20a%20portfolio%20career%20is%20naturally%20proactive%2C%20is%20excited%20about%20raising%20their%20hand%20for%20opportunities%20and%20pitching%20themself%2C%20is%20inspired%20and%20creatively%20energized%20by%20having%20a%20few%20things%20going%20on%20at%20once%2C%20and%20is%20a%20person%20who%20finds%20it%20really%20difficult%20or%20boring%20to%20describe%20themselves%20in%20one%20job%20title%2C%26quot%3B%20Abrahami%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMackenzie%20finds%20flexibility%2C%20work%20freedom%2C%20and%20earning%20potential%20as%20pros%20of%20a%20portfolio%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20work%20for%20yourself%20in%20a%20portfolio%20career%20structure%2C%20you're%20constantly%20selling%2C%20and%20you're%20constantly%20negotiating%20deals%20and%20projects%20and%20so%20forth%2C%26quot%3B%20Mackenzie%20said.%20%26quot%3BYour%20earning%20capacity%20is%20really%20infinite%2C%20particularly%20if%20you%20start%20to%20productize%20your%20knowledge%20and%20build%20scalable%20income%20that%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20pro%20could%20be%20being%20able%20to%20focus%20on%20your%20strengths.%20Abrahami%20said%20her%20favorite%20part%20of%20building%20a%20portfolio%20career%20is%20%26quot%3Bfinally%26quot%3B%20being%20able%20to%20play%20to%20her%20strengths%2C%20like%20public%20speaking%2C%20because%20she%20can%20decide%20what%20jobs%20she%20pursues.%20Abrahami%20is%20a%20career%20coach%20and%20a%20career%20education%20strategist%20for%20universities%2C%20MBA%20programs%2C%20and%20professional%20associations.%20She%20also%20creates%20social%20media%20content%2C%20works%20with%20brands%2C%20has%20a%20newsletter%2C%20and%20does%20public%20speaking%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20full-time%2C%20corporate%20jobs%2C%20yes%2C%20I%20had%20roles%20where%20they%20played%20to%20my%20strengths%2C%20but%20I%20was%20often%20really%20catching%20up%20on%20my%20opportunities%20for%20growth%2C%20and%20there%20was%20never%20one%20role%20where%20I%20was%20like%2C%20'I'm%20a%20natural%20for%20this%2C'%26quot%3B%20Abrahami%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20a%20portfolio%20career%20has%20its%20cons%2C%20such%20as%20being%20overwhelmed%20by%20too%20much%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPortfolio%20careers%20give%20us%20much%20more%20flexibility%20if%20we%20choose%20that%2C%20but%20it%20also%20is%20a%20double-edged%20sword%20because%20if%20you%20add%20so%20many%20jobs%20and%20part-time%20gigs%20and%20freelance%20opportunities%20to%20your%20portfolio%20career%2C%20you%20can%20just%20as%20easily%20overwhelm%20yourself%20and%20be%20working%20a%20lot%20harder%20and%20a%20lot%20longer%20than%20you%20would%20in%20one%209-to-5%2C%26quot%3B%20Abrahami%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMackenzie%20finds%20having%20less%20financial%20stability%20and%20less%20work%20security%20compared%20to%20a%20full-time%20role%20is%20a%20risk%20of%20a%20portfolio%20career%20and%20that%20loneliness%20could%20be%20another%20con.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTypically%2C%20people%20are%20working%20by%20themselves%2C%20or%20they're%20dipping%20in%20and%20out%20of%20teams%20and%20dipping%20in%20and%20out%20of%20the%20projects%2C%26quot%3B%20Mackenzie%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that's%20one%20of%20the%20things%20that%20I%20see%20people%20in%20this%20space%20struggle%20with%20is%20this%20lack%20of%20camaraderie%20and%20community.%20And%20it%20just%20means%20that%20you%20have%20to%20intentionally%20create%20that%20for%20yourself%2C%20whether%20you%20join%20established%20communities%20or%20you%20go%20to%20a%20coworking%20space.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20made%20a%20switch%20to%20a%20portfolio%20career%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20share%20what%20this%20career%20change%20has%20been%20like.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-portfolio-career-pros-cons-income-streams-side-hustles-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726306922000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e44490cfb7f307e5715ccd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-portfolio-career-pros-cons-income-streams-side-hustles-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20portfolio%20career%20has%20pros%20and%20cons%2C%20but%20it%20might%20be%20ideal%20in%20the%20new%2C%20flexible%20work%20era.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-portfolio-career-pros-cons-income-streams-side-hustles-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22There%20are%202%20kinds%20of%20cities%20right%20now.%20It%20explains%20why%20you%20hate%20your%20downtown.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20smaller%20and%20duller%20city%20next%20to%20a%20bright%20and%20shiny%20larger%20city%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66df4358a0ff598b2665e7bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EWestend61%2FGetty%2C%20Huber%20%26amp%3B%20Starke%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAmerican%20downtowns%20are%20struggling%20post-pandemic%20and%20turning%20to%20tourism%20to%20revive%20activity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDowntowns%20that%20serve%20residents%20with%20diverse%20amenities%20attract%20more%20tourists%20than%20event-based%20areas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWaterfronts%20and%20public%20markets%20are%20key%20attractions%2C%20while%20walkability%20and%20housing%20boost%20local%20vibrancy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20American%20downtowns%20are%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmidwest-america-cities-downtown-crisis-office-apocalypse-urban-doom-loop-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruggling%20to%20bounce%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20pandemic-induced%20remote%20work%2C%20which%20has%20emptied%20office%20buildings%20and%20hit%20local%20businesses%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20scramble%20to%20get%20people%20back%20downtown%2C%20many%20are%20turning%20to%20tourism.%20Sometimes%2C%20that%20means%20prioritizing%20visitors%20over%20locals.%20But%20ignoring%20quality%20of%20life%20for%20those%20who%20call%20a%20place%20home%20can%20backfire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20kinds%20of%20downtowns%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0those%20that%20cater%20to%20their%20residents%20and%20those%20that%20cater%20to%20tourists%2C%20said%20Jon%20Jon%20Wesolowski%2C%20an%20urbanist%20with%20a%20popular%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Fdiscover%2Fjon-jon-wesolowski%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%20account%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETourist-focused%20downtowns%20are%20mostly%20centered%20around%20large%20event%20venues%2C%20like%20stadiums%20and%20convention%20centers%2C%20attractions%20like%20museums%20and%20monuments%2C%20and%20lots%20of%20hotels.%20This%20characterizes%20downtowns%20from%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20to%20Chattanooga%2C%20Tennessee.%20Resident-centered%20urban%20cores%20have%20lots%20of%20housing%2C%20public%20amenities%20like%20schools%20and%20parks%2C%20and%20local%20restaurants%2C%20shops%2C%20and%20other%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nation's%20capital%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2Fmagazine%2F2024%2F03%2F01%2Fdowntown-dc-transformation-plan-00144253%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffers%20a%20stark%20example%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20downtown%20designed%20largely%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fdc-md-va%2F2024%2F03%2F15%2Fdowntown-dc-bowser-crime-offices-vacancy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eserve%20office%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20tourists.%20Half-empty%20federal%20office%20buildings%2C%20boarded-up%20storefronts%2C%20and%20national%20museums%20that%20sit%20empty%20after%206%20p.m.%20make%20downtown%20an%20unwelcoming%20place%20for%20residents.%20To%20the%20city's%20credit%2C%20it's%20working%20to%20change%20that%20by%20adding%20thousands%20of%20homes%20downtown%2C%20in%20part%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcwashington.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fmayor-bowser-unveils-major-office-to-housing-conversion-in-downtown-dc%2F3662210%2F%3Fos%3Dio.%26ref%3Dapp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econverting%20vacant%20office%20buildings%20into%20apartments%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20American%20downtowns%20just%20don't%20have%20regular%20people%20that%20live%20there%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20either%20priced%20out%20because%20of%20real%20estate%2C%20or%20there%20just%20isn't%20much%20there%20to%20attract%20the%20type%20of%20people%20that%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20that%20much%20for%20the%20real%20estate%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Wesolowski%2C%20who%20recently%20announced%20a%20run%20for%20city%20council%20in%20his%20hometown%20of%20Chattanooga%2C%20Tennessee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20it's%20the%20downtowns%20designed%20for%20locals%C2%A0that%20tourists%20love%20the%20most%2C%20he%20argues.%20Visitors%20are%20more%20attracted%20to%20%26quot%3Blively%26quot%3B%20downtowns%20that%20are%20busy%2018%20hours%20a%20day%20because%20people%20live%2C%20work%2C%20and%20play%20there%2C%20rather%20than%20%26quot%3Bprogram-based%26quot%3B%20urban%20cores%20that%20revolve%20around%20big%20events%20%E2%80%94%20like%20sports%20games%20and%20concerts%20%E2%80%94%20and%20are%20otherwise%20dead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETourist-filled%20cities%20like%20Paris%20and%20Chicago%20are%20attractive%20because%20%26quot%3Bthey%20feel%20like%20real%20places%2C%26quot%3B%20Wesolowski%20says.%20While%20visitors%20might%20snap%20a%20photo%20in%20front%20of%20the%20Eiffel%20Tower%20or%20the%20Bean%2C%20they%20visit%20downtown%20because%20of%20the%20diverse%20array%20of%20things%20to%20do%20and%20see%20that%20locals%20created%20and%20patronize.%20Think%20of%20Paris'%20many%20sidewalk%20cafes%20or%20the%20music%20venues%20in%20Chicago's%20Wicker%20Park.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20places%20aren't%20trying%20to%20please%20tourists%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Wesolowski.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20trying%20to%20serve%20their%20citizens.%20And%20their%20citizens%20are%20so%20well%20served%20that%20we%20long%20for%20those%20places.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280240ab1-b61f-4bfe-aacf-e62d978b369c%5C%22%3EThe%20unsexy%20way%20to%20get%20people%20downtown%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20cities%20focus%20on%20bringing%20in%20visitors%2C%20they%20need%20to%20serve%20their%20residents%2C%20Wesolowski%20argued.%20That%20involves%20the%20notably%20less%20sexy%20work%20of%20making%20sure%20there's%20sufficient%20housing%20and%20mass%20transit%20downtown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20downtowns%20are%20walkable%20and%20bikeable%2C%20people%20can%20live%20more%20densely%2C%20and%20pedestrians%20are%20likelier%20to%20spend%20money%20at%20local%20businesses.%20The%20more%20pedestrians%2C%20the%20healthier%20the%20urban%20core%2C%20Wesolowski%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20think%20of%20the%20downtown%20as%20an%20ecosystem%2C%20think%20of%20pedestrians%20as%20the%20indicator%20species%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20lots%20of%20people%20live%2C%20walk%2C%20and%20bike%20downtown%2C%20they%20turn%20it%20into%20a%20lively%2024-hour%20neighborhood%20with%20various%20amenities%2C%20including%20restaurants%2C%20shops%2C%20and%20entertainment.%20These%20amenities%2C%20paired%20with%20the%20city's%20investments%20in%20public%20spaces%2C%20parks%2C%20and%20transit%2C%20naturally%20attract%20tourists%20but%20also%20survive%20when%20tourism%20dips%2C%20like%20it%20did%20during%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chicago%20River%2C%20the%20River%20walk%2C%20Kayaks%20and%20surrounding%20downtown%20architecture%20in%20summer%2C%20Chicago%2C%20Illinois.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e344dfd17aa3c7b2b233c3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChicago%20has%20multiple%20well-used%20waterfronts%2C%20including%20its%20Riverwalk.%3Cp%3EJumping%20Rocks%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224b278cf4-9598-41f1-b7fa-83d190448057%5C%22%3EThe%20best%20kind%20of%20tourist%20attractions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20one-size-fits-all%20strategy%20for%20boosting%20tourism%20in%20American%20cities.%20There's%20no%20universal%20balance%20between%20visitors%2C%20residents%2C%20and%20workers%20and%20no%20single%20strategy%20to%20maximize%20economic%20development%20and%20social%20good%2C%20said%20Tracy%20Hadden%20Loh%2C%20a%20fellow%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20who%20studies%20downtowns%20and%20urban%20real%20estate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20amenities%20with%20many%20uses%20and%20offerings%20satisfying%20a%20diverse%20array%20of%20people%C2%A0tend%20to%20work%20best.%20The%20nonprofit%20Project%20for%20Public%20Spaces%20describes%20this%20phenomenon%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pps.org%2Farticle%2Fthe-power-of-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPower%20of%2010%2B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20holds%20that%20places%20thrive%20when%20people%20have%2010%20or%20more%20reasons%20to%20be%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20flip%20side%2C%20amenities%20like%20convention%20centers%20and%20big%20stadiums%2C%20which%20tend%20to%20be%20car-centric%20and%20infrequently%20used%2C%20aren't%20the%20best%20uses%20of%20space.%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20multi-purpose%20your%20facilities%20could%20be%2C%20the%20better%20off%20you%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Karen%20Chapple%2C%20director%20of%20the%20School%20of%20Cities%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20most%20attractive%20amenities%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Furban-doom-loop-beaches-parks-cities-rivers-swimming-waterfronts-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewaterfront%20parks%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20public%20markets.%20Waterfronts%20are%20%26quot%3Bunparalleled%20in%20their%20ability%20to%20be%20all%20things%20to%20all%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Loh%20said.%20Parks%20along%20urban%20rivers%2C%20lakes%2C%20canals%2C%20and%20ocean%20beaches%20can%20attract%20new%20residents%2C%20visitors%2C%20and%20commercial%20development%20while%20serving%20as%20a%20buffer%20for%20flooding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20markets%20are%20%26quot%3Ba%20really%20special%20kind%20of%20infrastructure%20that%20can%20serve%20both%20people%20who%20go%20downtown%20every%20day%20and%20people%20who%20are%20there%20for%20the%20first%20time%20from%20really%20far%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can%20program%20them%20in%20bite-sized%20pieces%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20public%20market%20isn't%20just%20one%20vendor%2C%26quot%3B%20Loh%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20similarly%2C%20a%20waterfront%20isn't%20just%20one%20activity.%20It's%20actually%20dozens%20or%20hundreds%20of%20activities%20that%20can%20all%20take%20place%20at%20the%20same%20time%20in%20the%20same%20setting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChapple%20pointed%20to%20San%20Diego's%20downtown%20as%20a%20strong%20example%20of%20a%20diversified%20place%20with%20an%20attractive%20waterfront.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20a%20really%20quite%20an%20extraordinary%20balance%20of%20tourist%20facilities%2C%20local%20universities%2C%20medical%20complexes%2C%20residents%20living%20downtown%2C%20a%20baseball%20team%20downtown%2C%20a%20waterfront%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it%20sort%20of%20does%20everything%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20The%20balmy%20weather%20year-round%20is%20also%20a%20huge%20perk%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0there's%20no%20time%20of%20year%20when%20San%20Diego's%20outdoor%20spaces%20aren't%20usable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2-kinds-of-cities-explains-why-you-hate-your-downtown-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726306622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66df4358a0ff598b2665e7bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2-kinds-of-cities-explains-why-you-hate-your-downtown-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20struggling%20downtowns%20are%20relying%20on%20tourism%20to%20bounce%20back%20from%20the%20pandemic.%20That%20might%20be%20a%20mistake.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2-kinds-of-cities-explains-why-you-hate-your-downtown-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gyms%20are%20scrambling%20to%20add%20squat%20racks%20for%20the%20strength-training%20renaissance%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20squat%20rack%20amid%20a%20bunch%20of%20treadmills%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c635f9b4912df3ae1d8375%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVenture%20into%20any%20commercial%20gym%20during%20peak%20hours%2C%20and%20you'll%20likely%20see%20the%20same%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERow%20after%20row%20of%20empty%20treadmills%2C%20stair%20climbers%2C%20and%20elliptical%20trainers.%20Meanwhile%2C%20crowds%20of%20people%20are%20swamped%20around%20the%20squat%20racks%2C%20benches%2C%20and%20free%20weights%2C%20waiting%20to%20pounce%20on%20the%20first%20free%20piece%20of%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELong%20cardio%20sessions%20are%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past.%20Now%2C%20everyone%20and%20their%20mother%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprofessor-exercise-aging-workout-food-longevity-karyn-esser-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliterally%3C%2Fa%3E)%20is%20into%20squats.%20And%20deadlifts.%20And%20hip%20thrusts.%20And%20a%20multitude%20of%20other%20strength-building%20moves%2C%20especially%20ones%20that%20help%20sculpt%20a%20powerful%20lower%20body.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20from%20the%20Sports%20and%20Fitness%20Industry%20Association%2C%20the%20major%20trade%20association%20for%20sports%20equipment%20manufacturers%20and%20fitness%20brands%2C%20illuminates%20this%20trend.%20Since%202019%2C%20gym-goers%20have%20been%20ditching%20the%20ellipticals%20and%20stair%20climbers%2C%20reaching%20instead%20for%20kettlebells%20and%20free%20weights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FFNAky%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Fastest-growing%20gym%20activities%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22282%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20just%20one%20problem%3A%20most%20commercial%20gyms%20are%20not%20equipped%20for%20this%20shift%20in%20consumer%20preferences.%20They're%20becoming%20a%20graveyard%20for%20bulky%2C%20old%20cardio%20machines%20with%20dated%20plugs%20and%20grainy%20televisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FEKqaH%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Fastest-declining%20gym%20activities%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22282%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EGym%20owners%20are%20aware.%20%26quot%3BTrust%20me%2C%20our%20members%20will%20come%20up%20to%20us%20and%20tell%20us%20exactly%20how%20they%20feel%2C%26quot%3B%20Mauro%20Maietta%2C%20district%20fitness%20manager%20at%20Crunch%20Fitness%20in%20Manhattan%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20some%20locations%20where%20they're%20like%2C%20okay%2C%20what's%20with%20the%2040%20treadmills%3F%20We%20need%20more%20benches.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20remodeling%20a%20gym%20is%20not%20simple.%20The%20process%20is%20slow%2C%20expensive%2C%20and%20complicated.%20It's%20often%20easier%20to%20swap%20out%20an%20old%20elliptical%20for%20some%20new%20cardio%20machine%2C%20even%20if%20that's%20not%20what%20people%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECardio%20created%20the%20gym%20industry%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20the%201960s%2C%20fitness%20trends%20didn't%20really%20exist.%20Gyms%20were%20for%20children.%20Kids%20played%20sports%2C%20ran%20track%20and%20field%2C%20and%20did%20Presidential%20Fitness%20Tests%20at%20school%2C%20but%20adults%20didn't%20have%20time%20for%20such%20childish%20games.%20That%20all%20changed%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhealth.usnews.com%2Fhealth-news%2Fblogs%2Feat-run%2Farticles%2Fthe-evolution-of-fitness-trends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKenneth%20Cooper%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Baerobics%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20type%20of%20high-energy%20exercise%20that%20he%20said%20would%20reduce%20your%20risk%20of%20cardiovascular%20disease.%20Or%2C%20for%20short%3A%20cardio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuddenly%2C%20exercise%20wasn't%20just%20a%20fun%20activity.%20A%20new%20idea%20was%20taking%20hold%2C%20that%20jumping%2C%20running%2C%20jazzercizing%2C%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20bouncing%20around%20are%20%3Cem%3Eimportant%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20your%20heart%20and%20your%20waistline.%20This%20cultural%20shift%20created%20a%20demand%20for%20places%20to%20work%20out.%20It%20created%20the%20gym%20industry%2C%20and%20cardio%20was%20the%20driving%20force.%20Sure%2C%20there%20was%20muscle%20beach%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20L.A.%2C%20which%20had%20been%20around%20since%20the%201930s%2C%20but%20that%20turf%20was%20largely%20reserved%20for%20the%20ultra-shredded%20Arnold%20Schwarzeneggers%20of%20the%20world%20who%20wanted%20to%20%3Cem%3Elook%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20certain%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20with%20the%20cardio-centric%20gym%20was%20that%20it%20stemmed%20from%20a%20half-baked%20understanding%20of%20fitness.%20Cardio%20certainly%20plays%20a%20role%20in%20heart%20health%20and%20longevity%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20whole%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Richard%20Simmons%20working%20out%20with%20people%20behind%20him%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65fc10872417f97b87cdf928%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221515%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENo%20offense%2C%20Richard%20Simmons%2C%20but%20cardio%20is%20out.%3Cp%3EEvan%20Hurd%20Photography%2FSygma%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20past%20couple%20of%20decades%20have%20seen%20a%20boom%20in%20science%20showing%20that%20resistance%20training%20has%20a%20wealth%20of%20benefits%2C%20beyond%20looking%20big%20and%20strong.%20Lifting%20weights%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimprove-mobility-build-muscle-longevity-exercise-personal-trainer-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelp%20you%20feel%20younger%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20longer%2C%20delay%20chronic%20illness%2C%20boost%20bone%20health%2C%20and%20reduce%20pain.%20It%20may%20even%20improve%20your%20self-image.%20Weight-lifting%20isn't%20even%20necessarily%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Ffitness%2Fweight-lifting-myths-for-women%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egetting%20big%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20it%20can%20actually%20help%20you%20stay%20lean%20and%20toned.%20In%20fact%2C%20studies%20show%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstrength-training-better-cardio-burning-fat-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estrength%20training%20beats%20cardio%2C%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20fat%20burning%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20the%20evidence%20is%20showing%20is%20that%20building%20muscle%20through%20strength%20training%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20using%20cardio%20to%20manage%20weight%2C%20has%20a%20much%20greater%20effect%20on%20promoting%20longevity%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%26quot%3BSmarter%20Workouts%26quot%3B%20author%20and%20fitness%20industry%20consultant%20Pete%20McCall%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20while%20scientists%20and%20trainers%20have%20known%20this%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20it%20has%20taken%20a%20while%20to%20catch%20on%20more%20broadly.%20Before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20studio%20classes%2C%20like%20spin%2C%20were%20booming.%20From%202018%20to%202019%2C%20gym-goers%20were%20hungry%20for%20cycling%2C%20stair%20climbing%2C%20and%20rowing%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Fitness%20Association%2C%20the%20trade%20group%20representing%20gyms%2C%20studios%2C%20and%20the%20fitness%20industry%20at%20large%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECOVID%20triggered%20a%20sharp%20pivot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20boom%20of%20strength%20training%20in%202020%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223997%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kayla%20Itsines%20Profile%20%20%20Rooftop%20copy%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F600ec3a77e47190011cb8fad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222599%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAustralian%20personal%20trainer%20Kayla%20Itsines%20developed%20the%20uber%20popular%20%26quot%3BSweat%20with%20Kayla%26quot%3B%20app.%3Cp%3EKayla%20Itsines%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20months%20of%202020%2C%20people%20working%20out%20at%20home%20turned%20to%20social%20media%20influencers%20and%20personal%20trainers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20extolled%20the%20benefits%20of%20resistance%20training.%20By%20June%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fweights-dumbbells-not-in-stock-online-many-retailers-gyms-closed-2020-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20had%20run%20out%20of%20barbells%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20dumbbells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFitness%20influencers%20had%20been%20driving%20an%20interest%20in%20strength%20training%20since%20the%20dawn%20of%20Instagram%20in%20the%20mid-2010s%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20niche%20trend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20suddenly%2C%20influencers%20like%20Kayla%20Itsines%2C%20Kira%20Stokes%2C%20and%20Kaisa%20Keranen%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffitness-influencer-industry-pandemic-quarantine-boom-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eamassing%20millions%20more%20followers%20around%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Fans%2C%20pent%20up%20in%20their%20living%20rooms%2C%20navigating%20the%20unclear%20perils%20of%20a%20new%20pandemic%2C%20wanted%20to%20feel%20strong%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20look%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWomen%20used%20to%20have%20this%20misconception%20that%20if%20they%20did%20strength%20training%2C%20they'd%20become%20too%20muscular%2C%26quot%3B%20Pamela%20Kufahl%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20communications%20at%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Fitness%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20But%20consumers%20are%20getting%20savvier.%20Kufahl%20says%20from%20Gen%20Z%20to%20elders%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20real%20and%20growing%20recognition%20of%20the%20importance%20of%20strength%20training%20for%20longevity%20and%20even%20mental%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egyms%20reopened%2C%20members%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eare%20spending%20more%20time%20muscle-building%20and%20less%20time%20on%20cardio%20machines%2C%20the%20Health%20%26amp%3B%20Fitness%20data%20shows.%20People%20%E2%80%94%20in%20particular%2C%20women%20%E2%80%94%20are%20investing%20more%20of%20their%20gym%20dollars%20into%20personal%20training%20sessions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDemand%20for%20unique%2C%20personalized%20fitness%20has%20upended%20the%20point%20of%20the%20gym.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20days%2C%20people%20aren't%20going%20to%20the%20gym%20for%20solo%20elliptical%20sessions%2C%20they're%20joining%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frun-club-making-friends-dating-app-alternatives-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erun%20clubs%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20work%20up%20a%20sweat%20(and%20maybe%20even%20find%20love).%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fathletechnews.com%2Fboutique-fitness-personal-training-gen-z-millennials-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBoutique%20group%20fitness%20classes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20Pure%20Barre%20and%20Orange%20Theory%2C%20are%20proliferating%2C%20and%20membership%20is%20growing%20at%20boot%20camps%20like%20CrossFit.%20Pilates%20%E2%80%94%20low-impact%20resistance%20training%20that%20touts%20strength%20and%20longevity%20%E2%80%94%20is%20soaring%20in%20popularity%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finsider.fitt.co%2Fissue-no-300-powerhouse%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFitt%20Insider%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20been%20in%20any%20large%20gym%2C%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20pore%20over%20industry%20reports%20or%20financial%20filings%20to%20tell%20you%20all%20this%20is%20true.%20These%20days%2C%20cardio%20is%20just%20one%20part%20of%20fitness.%20Treadmills%2C%20while%20still%20the%20most%20popular%2C%20least%20intimidating%20piece%20of%20equipment%20in%20the%20gym%20overall%2C%20might%20be%20used%20for%20a%20warmup%20or%20cooldown%2C%20not%20the%20entire%20workout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22soccer%20players%20training%20at%20gym%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e47fa9d17aa3c7b2b28c79%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFunctional%20fitness%20is%20in.%3Cp%3EAntonio%20Villalba%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMcCall%2C%20who%20is%20a%20consultant%20for%20the%20cardio%20icon%20StairMaster%2C%20says%20this%20trend%20is%20only%20just%20getting%20started.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20going%20to%20see%20a%20lot%20more%20interest%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years%20in%20strength%20training%20from%20all%20age%20groups%2C%26quot%3B%20McCall%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BThe%2020-somethings%2C%20the%2040-somethings%2C%20the%2060-somethings%20will%20all%20be%20gravitating%20towards%20strength%20training%2C%20just%20because%20of%20the%20benefits%20it%20provides.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20conundrum%20for%20gyms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20sharp%20shift%20requires%20some%20adjustment%20for%20gym%20owners.%20In%20most%20gyms%2C%20the%20weight%20section%20is%20one%20small%20corner%20of%20their%20floor%20plan%2C%20and%20it%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20crowded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSuddenly%2C%20now%20they%20need%20more%20plate-loaded%20equipment%2C%20they%20need%20to%20find%20space%20for%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Kufahl%20said.%20%26quot%3BStrength%20equipment%20takes%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20space%2C%20they%20need%20to%20be%20bolted%20in.%20To%20move%20strength%20equipment%20around%20is%20a%20big%20task%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20gym%20operators%20and%20it%20requires%20some%20planning%2C%20it%20requires%20determining%20what%20to%20do%20with%20the%20flooring.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Olympic-level%20runner%20Eilish%20McColgan%20training%20on%20squat%20rack%20at%20home%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e480c7bf0250c214935001%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIf%20you're%20an%20Olympic-level%20pro%20runner%2C%20like%20the%20UK's%20Eilish%20McColgan%2C%20keeping%20a%20squat%20rack%20at%20home%20makes%20sense.%20But%20for%20most%20of%20us%2C%20it%20doesn't.%3Cp%3EClive%20Brunskill%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20fully%20outfit%20a%201%2C300-2%2C800-square-foot%20gym%20for%20strength-training%2C%20you%20need%20dumbbells%2C%20kettlebells%2C%20barbells%2C%20medicine%20balls%2C%20three%20to%20four%20racks%2C%20and%20flooring%20that%20can%20withstand%20heavy%20weights.%20That%20takes%20around%20%2460-75%2C000%2C%20Chris%20Travis%2C%20owner%20and%20coach%20at%20Seattle%20Strength%20and%20Performance%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20it's%20a%20higher%20initial%20cost%20for%20gyms%20to%20buy%20that%20strength%20equipment%2C%20because%20it's%20designed%20to%20last%20a%20lot%20longer%20than%20treadmills%2C%20ellipticals%2C%20or%20stair%20climbers%2C%20which%20might%20be%20on%20a%20multi-year%20lease%2C%20and%20have%20lots%20of%20electronics%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusinesses%20can't%20bend%20to%20every%20new%20trend%2C%20but%20consultants%20say%20it's%20time%20to%20do%20this%20remodeling%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20COVID%2C%20gyms%20have%20struggled%20to%20keep%20their%20members.%20Last%20month%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.press.blinkfitness.com%2Fblink-fitness-takes-action-to-position-business-for-future%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlink%20Fitness%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20the%20cheaper%2C%20most%20basically-equipped%20gyms%20in%20the%20New%20York%20City%20area%20filed%20for%20bankruptcy%2C%20signaling%20a%20realization%20that%20many%20before-%20and%20after-work%20gym%20crowds%20just%20aren't%20coming%20back.%20But%20Blink's%20parent%20company%20Equinox%2C%20a%20luxury%20brand%20with%20plenty%20of%20space%20for%20personal%20trainers%20and%20kettlebell%20racks%2C%20plus%20one%20elite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fequi