%20Whatnot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EZapata%20first%20heard%20about%20a%20platform%20called%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whatnot.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWhatnot%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20when%20one%20of%20the%20creators%20she%20followed%20on%20YouTube%20ended%20a%20video%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BCatch%20us%20on%20Whatnot!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20like%2C%20'What%20is%20Whatnot%3F'%26quot%3B%20she%20recalled.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20obviously%20going%20to%20go%20catch%20them%20on%20Whatnot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EZapata%20downloaded%20the%20app%20and%20learned%20that%20it's%20a%20marketplace%20that%20allows%20sellers%20to%20host%20live%20shows%20and%20sell%20products%20in%20real%20time.%20She%20joined%20a%20show%2C%20and%20it%20was%20unlike%20anything%20she'd%20ever%20experienced.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20crazy.%20There%20were%20shows%20that%20were%20happening%20with%20600%2C%20700%2C%20800%20people.%20People%20were%20buying%20things%20in%20under%20three%20seconds%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20described.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20Facebook%20or%20Twitter%20met%20eBay.%20It%20was%20so%20much%20fun%20when%20I%20started%20watching%2C%20and%20I%20was%20like%2C%20'Oh%20man%2C%20I%20would%20be%20really%20good%20at%20this.%20This%20is%20totally%20my%20personality.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20applied%20and%20got%20approved%20to%20sell%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20but%20didn't%20start%20hosting%20shows%20immediately.%20She%20shadowed%20a%20friend%20who%20was%20also%20starting%20to%20do%20live%20Whatnot%20shows.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20a%20crash%20course%20of%20what%20to%20do%20and%20what%20not%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zapata.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStill%2C%20her%20first%20show%20was%20%26quot%3Bmayhem%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20profitable.%20%26quot%3BI%20made%20like%2050%20bucks.%20I%20was%20probably%20negative%20after%20the%20boxes.%20When%20I%20ran%20the%20numbers%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20'Oh%20my%20God%2C%20it%20took%20me%20forever%20to%20find%20these%20sneakers.'%20I%20think%20I%20might%20have%20even%20cried.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHer%20dad%20encouraged%20her%20to%20stick%20with%20it%2C%20comparing%20it%20to%20his%20industry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BMy%20dad%20knows%20that%20an%20F-150%20in%20Houston%20is%20going%20to%20get%20the%20most%20activity%2C%20whereas%2C%20you%20might%20not%20get%20that%20same%20activity%20in%20Nevada.%20He's%20like%2C%20'You're%20going%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20they%20want%2C%20what%20they%20don't%20want%2C%20and%20what%20they%20will%20bid%20for%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Zapata.%20%26quot%3BSlowly%20but%20surely%2C%20we%20started%20making%203%25%2C%204%25%2C%205%25%2C%20and%20then%20one%20day%20we%20made%2015%25%20And%20then%20one%20day%20we%20sold%20%2425%2C000%20in%20a%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22val%20zapata%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e48471d17aa3c7b2b28eda%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZapata%20has%20a%206%2C000-square-foot%20warehouse%20space%20in%20Las%20Vegas.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Val%20Zapata%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20majority%20of%20her%20sales%20now%20come%20from%20live%20Whatnot%20shows.%20In%20the%20beginning%2C%20she%20was%20hosting%20daily.%20She%20and%20her%20dad%20turned%20the%20game%20room%20of%20their%20family%20home%20into%20her%20studio.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20gotten%20a%20little%20techier%20now%2C%20but%20at%20the%20time%20it%20was%20just%20my%20iPad%2C%20so%20I%20could%20see%20the%20chat%2C%20and%20my%20iPhone%2C%20so%20the%20chat%20could%20see%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zapata.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20a%20little%20desk%20ring%20light.%20It%20was%20probably%2015%20bucks%20on%20Amazon.%20The%20backdrop%20was%20a%20couple%20of%20racks%20of%20sneakers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20her%20current%20streams%20are%20shorter%20one-%20to%20two-hour%20%26quot%3Bpower%20hours%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20her%20first%20few%20months%20on%20the%20platform%20she'd%20go%20live%20for%20multiple%20hours%20at%20a%20time.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20wake%20up%20so%20fried%20from%20eight%20or%20nine%20hours%20of%20really%20high%20intense%20energy%2C%20because%20we%20bring%20the%20show%2C%20and%20my%20dad%20would%20have%20set%20the%20stream%20back%20up%2C%20my%20background%20would%20be%20perfect%2C%20and%20that%20was%20just%20his%20way%20of%20continuing%20to%20encourage%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20just%20one%20month%20on%20Whatnot%2C%20Zapata%20says%20she%20did%20enough%20in%20sales%20to%20quit%20her%20insurance%20job%20in%20September%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20as%20of%20September%202024%2C%20she%20leads%20a%20team%20of%20eight%20employees%2C%20including%20her%20sister%2C%20who%20streams%20for%20The%20Shoe%20Game%20Co.%20in%20Houston.%20Zapata%20moved%20to%20Las%20Vegas%20in%20early%202024%20and%20rented%20a%206%2C000-square-foot%20warehouse%20to%20store%20product.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHer%20company%20has%20expanded%20to%20offering%20streetwear%20and%20has%20brought%20in%20up%20to%20%24500%2C000%20in%20sales%20a%20month.%20BI%20viewed%20her%20Whatnot%20seller%20dashboard%20and%20confirmed%20that%20her%20business%20has%20generated%20over%20%244%20million%20in%20sales%20so%20far%20in%202024%3C%2Fspan%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThis%20year%2C%20we're%20gunning%20for%20a%20million-dollar-a-month%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20the%2027-year-old%2C%20who%20says%20her%20life%20looks%20completely%20different%20than%20it%20did%20just%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20living%20at%20my%20parents'%20house%20for%20free.%20I%20now%20have%20this%20beautiful%20home%20in%20Vegas.%20I%20have%20a%20big%20warehouse.%20I%20actually%20have%20savings%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDon't%20underestimate%20the%20power%20of%20a%20hobby%2C%20she%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BWhatever%20time%20you%20can%20dedicate%20to%20a%20hobby%2C%20even%20if%20it's%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20that%20will%20pay%20off%20so%20much%20more%20than%20the%20eight%20or%20nine%20or%2010%20hours%20you're%20giving%20to%20your%209-to-5.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-a-gen-z-entrepreneur-built-seven-figure-resale-business-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726306022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e47d4dbf0250c214934e17%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-a-gen-z-entrepreneur-built-seven-figure-resale-business-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Val%20Zapata%20started%20reselling%20sneakers%20with%20her%20dad%20during%20the%20Covid%20pandemic%2C%20and%20eventually%20scaled%20the%20side%20project%20to%20a%20seven-figure%20business.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-a-gen-z-entrepreneur-built-seven-figure-resale-business-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22JD%20Vance's%20childcare%20plan%20ticked%20off%20some%20parents%20and%20grandparents.%20There's%20a%20way%20to%20fix%20it.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Photo%20collage%20featuring%20J.%20D.%20Vance%2C%20and%20close-up%20photos%20of%20mature%2Folder%20women's%20mouths%20with%20swear%20word%20speech%20bubbles%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e332c1bf0250c21492e2eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20countries%20pay%20family%2C%20friends%2C%20and%20neighbors%20who%20provide%20childcare%20services.%3Cp%3EDrew%20Hallowell%2FGetty%20Images%3B%20Alyssa%20Powell%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJD%20Vance%20recently%20suggested%20family%20members%20step%20in%20to%20help%20with%20childcare%20to%20cut%20costs%20for%20parents.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMany%20grandparents%20reached%20out%20to%20Business%20Insider%20expressing%20frustration%20with%20Vance's%20remarks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmerican%20families%20are%20facing%20both%20childcare%20and%20retirement%20crises.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ELinda%20C.%2C%20a%20retired%20deputy%20sheriff%20in%20California%2C%20considers%20herself%20politically%20independent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20voted%20for%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20in%202016%20and%20then%20for%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20in%202020.%20But%20this%20year%2C%20she%20feels%20strongly%20about%20supporting%20the%20Democratic%20ticket%2C%20largely%20because%20of%20the%20stances%20Republicans%2C%20including%20Trump's%20running%20mate%2C%20Sen.%20JD%20Vance%2C%20have%20taken%20on%20childcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20particularly%20perturbed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjd-vance-lower-childcare-costs-grandma-grandpa-help-retirement-crisis-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVance's%20recent%20suggestion%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20grandparents%20and%20other%20family%20members%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20out%20a%20little%20bit%20more%26quot%3B%20with%20childrearing%20to%20relieve%20the%20burden%20of%20childcare%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinda%20said%20she%20loves%20spending%20time%20with%20her%20grandchildren%20but%20worked%20hard%20for%20her%20retirement%20and%20thinks%20Vance's%20proposal%20is%20an%20unsustainable%20and%20%26quot%3Binsulting%26quot%3B%20solution%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DXksv2EGG9ek%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echildcare%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20a%20very%20intense%2C%20visceral%20response%20to%20it%2C%20almost%20like%20a%20PTSD%20response%20to%20it%2C%20because%20I%20was%20brought%20up%20in%20the%20'70s%20around%20what%20we%20used%20to%20call%20'male%20chauvinist%20pigs%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Linda%2C%20who%20requested%20her%20last%20name%20be%20withheld%20to%20protect%20her%20privacy.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20I'd%20never%20use%20that%20phrase%20again%2C%20but%20that's%20the%20way%20I'm%20feeling%20about%20Vance%20and%20Trump%20and%20the%20way%20that%20they're%20making%20women%20feel%20less%20than.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinda's%20daughter%20used%20to%20work%20as%20a%20dental%20assistant%20but%20quit%20when%20she%20had%20a%20kid%20because%20childcare%20was%20too%20expensive.%20%26quot%3BShe%20wants%20to%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Linda%20said.%20%26quot%3BShe%20wants%20to%20have%20a%20better%20lifestyle%20for%20her%20family%20to%20achieve%20the%20American%20dream.%20But%20she's%20unable%20to%20because%20it%20just%20doesn't%20pencil%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVance%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frepublican-baby-bust-panic-wont-support-pro-family-policies-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emany%20other%20conservative%3C%2Fa%3E%20lawmakers%20have%20opposed%20government%20subsidies%20for%20childcare%20providers%20in%20part%20because%20they%20say%20the%20policy%20prioritizes%20working%20parents%2C%20rather%20than%20those%20who%20stay%20home%20with%20their%20kids.%20After%20Vance's%20recent%20remarks%20on%20childcare%20drew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.salon.com%2F2024%2F09%2F10%2Fjd-vance-is-wrong-experts-say-boomer-grandparents-arent-the-solution-to-rising-day-care-costs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewidespread%20criticism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20clarified%20his%20stance%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FJDVance%2Fstatus%2F1831701121758589425%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bparents%20or%20grandparents%20might%20not%20be%20able%20to%20help%2C%20but%20they%20might%20want%20to%2C%20and%20for%20those%20families%2C%20federal%20policy%20should%20not%20be%20forcing%20one%20particular%20family%20model.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20reporting%20on%20Vance's%20remarks%2C%20Business%20Insider%20received%20a%20wave%20of%20reader%20emails%20expressing%20frustration%20that%20Vance%20was%20missing%20the%20point.%20Many%20said%20he%20failed%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20real%20reason%20many%20grandparents%20don't%20help%20with%20childcare%20more%3A%20They%20can't%20afford%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Vance's%20comments%20struck%20a%20nerve%20with%20some%20caregivers%20and%20weren't%20a%20fleshed-out%20policy%20idea%2C%20it's%20possible%20he's%20onto%20the%20beginnings%20of%20a%20solution%20that's%20helped%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20one%20expert%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Many%20American%20families%20are%20stuck%20between%20a%20retirement%20crisis%20and%20a%20childcare%20crisis%2C%20with%20young%20parents%20unable%20to%20help%20their%20own%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20and%20vice%20versa.%20As%20the%20economy%20takes%20center%20stage%20in%20the%20upcoming%20election%2C%20parents%20are%20watching%20both%20candidates%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20responding%20to%20the%20criticism%2C%20a%20spokeswoman%20for%20Vance%2C%20Taylor%20Van%20Kirk%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20vice%20presidential%20candidate%20believes%20the%20federal%20government%20should%20compensate%20family%20members%20and%20other%20kin%20for%20providing%20childcare.%20She%20also%20pointed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Famp%2Fnews%2Ftranscript-jd-vance-on-face-the-nation-aug-11-2024%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20comments%3C%2Fa%3E%20Vance%20made%20arguing%20that%20childcare%20subsidies%20shouldn't%20%26quot%3B%3Cspan%3Efavor%20one%20family%20model%20over%20another.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSenator%20Vance%2C%20who%20was%20raised%20largely%20by%20his%20own%20grandmother%2C%20knows%20firsthand%20the%20great%20sacrifice%20many%20grandparents%2C%20aunts%20and%20uncles%20and%20other%20relatives%20make%20when%20they%20care%20for%20a%20child%20who%20isn't%20their%20own%2C%26quot%3B%20Van%20Kirk%20said.%20%26quot%3BSenator%20Vance%20believes%20in%20addressing%20kinship%20care%20with%20federally%20supported%20initiatives%20so%20that%20these%20families%20are%20relieved%20of%20an%20enormous%2C%20oftentimes%20unseen%2C%20financial%20burden%20and%20have%20the%20necessary%20resources%20to%20care%20for%20these%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ed50e753-5c49-4632-aae6-32b9a90ea14d%5C%22%3EThe%20childcare%20crisis%20meets%20the%20retirement%20crisis%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESandra%2C%2051%2C%20has%20been%20dealing%20with%20both%20childcare%20and%20eldercare%20challenges%20over%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandra%2C%20who%20requested%20her%20last%20name%20be%20withheld%20to%20protect%20her%20family's%20privacy%2C%20has%20been%20taking%20care%20of%20her%20mother-in-law%2C%20who%20recently%20suffered%20an%20injury%2C%20while%20also%20helping%20to%20financially%20support%20her%20stepdaughter.%20She%20doesn't%20see%20herself%20having%20the%20time%20or%20the%20financial%20means%20to%20contribute%20to%20her%20children's%20potential%20childcare%20needs%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20goal%20is%20to%20one%20day%20retire.%20Our%20goal%20is%20to%20one%20day%20be%20able%20to%20put%20ourselves%20in%20a%20nursing%20home%20if%20we%20need%20that%2C%20and%20to%20not%20be%20the%20financial%20and%20also%20health%20caregiver%20burden%20on%20my%20stepdaughter%2C%26quot%3B%20Sandra%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20when%20she%20has%20children%2C%20would%20we%20love%20to%20be%20that%20grandma%20and%20grandpa%20that%20helped%20out%3F%20Absolutely.%20Do%20we%20know%20that%20we%20could%20physically%20or%20mentally%20do%20it%3F%20We're%20not%20sure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20looming%20retirement%20crisis%20is%20weighing%20on%20many%20older%20Americans.%20The%20Census%20Bureau's%20Population%20Survey%20found%20that%20more%20than%20half%20of%20respondents%20over%2065%20earned%20under%20%2430%2C000%20in%202022.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20an%20AARP%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.aarp.org%2F2024-4-24-New-AARP-Survey-1-in-5-Americans-Ages-50-Have-No-Retirement-Savings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20around%20one-fifth%20of%20adults%20aged%2050%20and%20older%20have%20no%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESandra%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bretirement%20feels%20completely%20out%20of%20reach%20for%20her.%26quot%3B%20While%20she%20earns%20income%20as%20a%20freelance%20writer%2C%20she%20and%20her%20husband%20are%20putting%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20financial%20resources%20toward%20helping%20the%20older%20members%20of%20their%20family%20and%20said%20that%20in%20her%20situation%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20'get%20grandma%20to%20help.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20like%20a%20very%20American%20problem%20that%20could%20be%20solved%2C%20but%20when%20you%20say%20things%20like%2C%20'just%20have%20grandma%20help%20out%20more%2C'%20that's%20a%20privilege%20that%20I%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20have%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElliot%20Haspel%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20nonpartisan%20family%20policy%20think%20tank%20Capita%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20there%20is%20a%20way%20to%20solve%20the%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Vance%20actually%20might%20be%20on%20the%20right%20track.%20While%20he%20acknowledged%20that%20Vance's%20comments%20lacked%20many%20important%20details%2C%20Haspel%20said%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20implementing%20more%20pathways%20to%20support%20family%2C%20friends%2C%20or%20neighbor%20caregivers%20%E2%80%94%20or%20FFNs%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20key%20way%20to%20address%20the%20childcare%20problem%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20better%20support%20of%20grandparents%20and%20other%20FFN%20caregivers%20was%20part%20of%20a%20comprehensive%20approach%20to%20childcare%2C%20then%20it%20can%20be%20really%20effective%20at%20making%20sure%20that%20American%20families%20have%20access%20to%20the%20options%20for%20care%20that%20they%20need%20and%20that%20are%20going%20to%20help%20their%20children%20develop%20healthily%2C%20and%20with%20the%20early%20learning%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20need%20to%20succeed%20later%2C%26quot%3B%20Haspel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20there's%20an%20opportunity%20here%20for%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20to%20expand%20on%20her%20childcare%20proposals%20in%20her%20platform%20%E2%80%94%20she%20has%20expressed%20support%20for%20national%20paid%20family%20leave%20and%20bolstered%20investments%20in%20childcare%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20address%20FFNs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20play%20out%20in%20a%20number%20of%20ways%3B%20for%20example%2C%20Haspel%20said%2C%20Sweden%20extended%20paid%20leave%20to%20grandparents%20wanting%20to%20take%20care%20of%20their%20grandchildren.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20US%20could%20require%20a%20comprehensive%20federal%20package%20to%20ensure%20sufficient%20funding%2C%20along%20with%20more%20robust%20investment%20in%20educational%20programs%20for%20child%20development%20%E2%80%94%20an%20idea%20Vance%20mentioned%20in%20his%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20be%20good%20for%20communities.%20It's%20going%20to%20be%20good%20for%20neighborhoods.%20It's%20going%20to%20be%20good%20for%20the%20economy.%20It's%20going%20to%20be%20good%20for%20social%20infrastructure%20and%20social%20connection%2C%26quot%3B%20Haspel%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20you%20can%20go%20down%20the%20line%20and%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20reasons%20to%20want%20a%20comprehensive%2C%20pluralistic%20approach%20to%20childcare.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJennifer%20Baker%2C%2040%2C%20found%20Vance's%20comments%20to%20be%20myopic%20and%20%26quot%3Bshockingly%20inadequate.%26quot%3B%20If%20parents%20had%20access%20to%20a%20familial%20network%2C%20she%20said%2C%20they'd%20probably%20already%20be%20taking%20advantage%20of%20it.%20For%20her%2C%20that's%20not%20an%20option%3A%20As%20a%20military%20spouse%2C%20Baker%20had%20to%20move%20away%20from%20her%20support%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20situation%20is%20not%20unique%2C%26quot%3B%20Baker%2C%20who's%20based%20in%20Arizona%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BMilitary%20families%20that%20are%20active%20duty%2C%20they%20go%20through%20long-term%20deployments%2C%20short%20tour%20deployments%2C%20they%20get%20relocated%20often%20every%20two%20years%20or%20four%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20her%2C%20figuring%20out%20childcare%20and%20balancing%20budgets%20has%20been%20a%20burden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20essentially%20forced%20to%20go%20back%20to%20work%20based%20on%20financial%20need%20weeks%2C%20if%20not%20months%2C%20before%20my%20body%20was%20physically%20ready%20for%20me%20to%20go%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAngela%20Rachidi%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20and%20Rowe%20Scholar%20at%20the%20right-leaning%20American%20Enterprise%20Institute%2C%20said%20that%20one%20underlying%20issue%20is%20that%20many%20mothers%20of%20younger%20children%20would%20prefer%20to%20work%20part-time%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20labor%20market%20isn't%20well%20structured%20to%20accommodate%20that%20type%20of%20work%2C%20especially%20for%20women%20who%20still%20want%20to%20develop%20their%20careers%20and%20career%20paths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20broader%20issue%20and%20something%20that%20both%20the%20private%20sector%20and%20employees%20can%20work%20out%20just%20trying%20to%20make%20the%20work%20schedules%20and%20the%20nature%20of%20work%20fit%20better%20with%20family%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Rachidi%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20would%20help%20parents%20who%20want%20to%20stay%20home%20and%20care%20for%20kids%3B%20it%20would%20also%20help%20grandparents%20who%20want%20to%20help%20care%20for%20kids%20while%20their%20parents%20are%20working.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERachidi%20also%20said%20that%20revisiting%20the%20usefulness%20of%20regulations%20around%20informal%20care%20%E2%80%94%20settings%20like%20friend%20and%20family%20care%20%E2%80%94%20should%20be%20on%20the%20table%2C%20too.%20Right%20now%2C%20she%20said%2C%20those%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aei.org%2Fopportunity-social-mobility%2Fthe-problem-with-child-care-regulations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eburdensome%20regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20drive%20up%20costs%2C%20and%20prevent%20providers%20from%20entering%20the%20market%20to%20begin%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERachidi%20also%20said%20that%20revisiting%20regulations%20around%20small%2C%20in-home%20childcare%20centers%20should%20be%20considered.%20Right%20now%2C%20she%20said%2C%20burdensome%20regulations%20can%20drive%20up%20costs%20and%20prevent%20small%20providers%20from%20starting%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnie%20Adler%2C%2076%2C%20is%20a%20retired%20physician%20and%20chair%20of%20the%20board%20of%20directors%20of%20Grandmothers%20for%20Reproductive%20Rights.%20She%20said%20that%20the%20assumption%20that%20grandparents%20are%20in%20a%20financial%20position%20to%20take%20time%20off%20to%20care%20for%20grandchildren%20is%20%26quot%3Bcrazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20grandmothers%20are%20working%20%E2%80%94%20and%20working%20because%20they%20need%20to%20work%20to%20pay%20the%20rent%20and%20need%20to%20work%20to%20try%20and%20save%20some%20money%20for%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Adler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bsafety%20net%20in%20this%20country%20is%20the%20unpaid%20work%20of%20women.%26quot%3B%20The%20unaffordability%20of%20childcare%20is%20a%20structural%20problem%2C%20she%20said%2C%20and%20it%20requires%20a%20structural%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20all%20the%20grandmothers%20in%20the%20country%20stopped%20working%20for%20a%20year%2C%20what%20will%20we%20do%20for%20doctors%20and%20nurses%20and%20teachers%20and%20scientists%20and%20engineers%20and%20bank%20tellers%20and%20everything%20else%3F%26quot%3B%20Adler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20a%20childcare%20worker%20with%20thoughts%20on%20JD%20Vance's%20comments%3F%20Share%20your%20story%20with%20these%20reporters%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejkaplan%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aerelman%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eerelman%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjd-vance-childcare-plan-grandparents-family-friends-neighbors-policy-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726305721000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e332d8bf0250c21492e2f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjd-vance-childcare-plan-grandparents-family-friends-neighbors-policy-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20JD%20Vance%20suggested%20grandparents%20help%20out%20more%20with%20childcare%2C%20many%20BI%20readers%20reached%20out%20expressing%20frustration%20that%20he%20was%20missing%20