arket%20faces%20risks%20from%20a%20deteriorating%20labor%20market.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWolfenbarger%20shared%205%20signs%20of%20a%20job%20market%20heading%20towards%20recession.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-recession-signals-sp500-outlook-unemployment-rate-wolfenbarger-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJon%20Wolfenbarger%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20stock%20market's%20success%20and%20the%20labor%20market's%20recent%20deterioration%20don't%20seem%20to%20add%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20market%20close%20on%20Friday%2C%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20sat%20at%205%2C626%2C%20just%20below%20record%20highs.%20And%20yet%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20continues%20to%20inch%20up%2C%20job%20openings%20continue%20to%20fall%2C%20and%20payroll%20data%20continue%20to%20underwhelm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20short%20explanation%20for%20this%20discrepancy%20is%20investor%20hype%20around%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20continued%20hope%20for%20an%20economic%20soft%20landing%2C%20according%20to%20Wolfenbarger%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20investing%20newsletter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbullandbearprofits.com%2Findex.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBullAndBearProfits.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20former%20investment%20banker%20at%20JPMorgan%20and%20Merrill%20Lynch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20long%20that%20enthusiasm%20can%20continue%20to%20outweigh%20declining%20labor%20market%20indicators%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20In%20a%20pair%20of%20notes%20this%20month%2C%20Wolfenbarger%20has%20laid%20out%20several%20pieces%20of%20evidence%20from%20job%20market%20data%20showing%20the%20outlook%20continuing%20to%20worsen%2C%20threatening%20to%20throw%20the%20economy%20into%20recession%20and%20lampoon%20the%20market's%20soft-landing%20hopes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20is%20declining%20job%20openings%2C%20which%20are%20down%20to%207.6%20million%20from%202022%20highs%20above%2012%20million.%20Since%20data%20started%20being%20collected%20in%20December%202000%2C%20the%20significant%20declines%20in%20job%20openings%20in%202001%2C%202008%2C%20and%202020%20were%20all%20accompanied%20by%20recessions.%20While%20openings%20have%20fallen%20a%20lot%2C%20however%2C%20they%20are%20still%20above%20pre-COVID%20levels%20and%20may%20just%20be%20normalizing%20after%20pandemic%20stimulus%20has%20dried%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20job%20openings%20data%20has%20had%20an%20impressively%20close%20correlation%20to%20stock%20market%20performance%20since%202000.%20This%20suggests%20the%20amount%20of%20job%20openings%20may%20have%20to%20turn%20around%20soon%2C%20or%20the%20market%20may%20be%20ahead%20of%20itself%20and%20in%20for%20a%20correction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHistorically%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20strong%20relationship%20between%20JOLTS%20openings%20(orange%20line)%20and%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20(blue%20line)%2C%20although%20there%20has%20been%20a%20major%20disconnect%20during%20the%20AI-driven%20rally%20of%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Wolfenbarger%20wrote%20in%20a%20September%209%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jolts%20and%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e4903fd17aa3c7b2b294b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221184%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBullAndBearProfits.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20sign%20Wolfenbarger%20shared%20showing%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20turning%20sour%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kansascityfed.org%2Fdata-and-trends%2Flabor-market-conditions-indicators%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKansas%20City%20Fed's%20Labor%20Market%20Conditions%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20composite%20of%2024%20job%20market%20indicators.%20The%20last%20three%20times%20is%20has%20climbed%20above%200.5%20and%20then%20declined%20again%20below%20that%20level%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20gone%20into%20recession.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indicator%20sits%20at%200.53%20right%20now%2C%20down%20from%201.4%20in%20May%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22construction%20employment%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e4905fbf0250c2149357ad%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22930%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBullAndBearProfits.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20the%20year-over-year%20percentage%20change%20in%20the%20employment%20level%2C%20or%20number%20of%20people%20employed.%20It%20just%20hit%200%25%2C%20and%20negative%20year-over-year%20growth%20has%20typically%20coincided%20with%20recessions%20over%20the%20last%20several%20decades%2C%20Wolfenbarger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222242%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22employment%20level%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e49078cfb7f307e571886f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22994%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBullAndBearProfits.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20employment%20growth%20is%20softening%2C%20there%20has%20also%20been%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20amount%20of%20part-time%20employees%20who%20cite%20economic%20reasons%20for%20taking%20part-time%20roles.%20Part-time%20employment%20levels%20usually%20surge%20during%20recessions%2C%20though%20current%20growth%20levels%20are%20not%20yet%20as%20pronounced%20as%20in%20prior%20downturns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222238%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22employment%20level%2C%20part%20time%20and%20full%20time%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e490a3d17aa3c7b2b294ec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22930%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBullAndBearProfits.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20in%20a%20September%202%20note%2C%20Wolfenbarger%20shared%20a%20chart%20from%20Bank%20of%20America%20showing%20the%20decline%20in%20private%20job%20growth%20as%20a%20share%20of%20all%20job%20growth.%20The%20chart%20excludes%20the%20healthcare%20and%20education%20sectors%2C%20which%20are%20typically%20immune%20to%20economic%20downturns.%20Private%20job%20growth%20is%20an%20important%20measure%20because%20it%20takes%20government%20payroll%20growth%20out%20of%20the%20equation%2C%20which%20is%20also%20resistant%20to%20business%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22private%20sector%20jobs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e490eabf0250c2149357ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22685%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBullAndBearProfits.com%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c27330a4-e5f7-49ce-aae9-9131a2b67c3a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWolfenbarger's%20views%20in%20context%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWolfenbarger%20sees%20the%20potential%20for%20severe%20downside%20for%20stocks.%20In%20an%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider%20on%20Friday%2C%20he%20confirmed%20that%20he%20continues%20to%20see%20a%20drop%20of%20as%20much%20as%2070%25%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20as%20plausible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cites%20John%20Hussman's%20valuation%20metric%20of%20the%20market-cap%20of%20non-financial%20stocks-to-the%20gross%20value-added%20of%20those%20stocks.%20With%20the%20measure%20currently%20at%20all-time-highs%2C%20Hussman%20said%20in%20August%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20would%20have%20to%20fall%20around%2070%25%20to%20get%20to%20levels%20where%20investors%20could%20expect%2010%25%20annualized%20returns%20over%20the%20following%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221204%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hussman%20funds%20potential%20market%20losses%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e4a0d1bf0250c2149361e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22711%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EHussman%20Funds%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20goes%20without%20saying%20that%20this%20is%20an%20extreme%20scenario%20and%20well%20outside%20of%20consensus%20on%20Wall%20Street.%20But%20a%20market%20decline%20of%20some%20significance%20is%20not%20out%20of%20the%20question%20if%20the%20economy%20does%20continue%20to%20soften%20beyond%20what%20investors%20are%20comfortable%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStocks%20sold%20off%20after%20the%20July%20and%20August%20jobs%20reports%20came%20in%20below%20expectations.%20The%20longer%20the%20streak%20of%20poor%20payrolls%20print%20extends%2C%20the%20higher%20the%20risk%20of%20recession%20will%20appear%20to%20investors%2C%20and%20the%20sharper%20potential%20market%20declines%20could%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20expected%20to%20start%20slashing%20interest%20rates%20next%20week%20to%20help%20the%20economy%20land%20on%20its%20feet%20after%20an%20inflation%20surge%2C%20and%20markets%20believe%20the%20central%20bank%20will%20reduce%20the%20benchmark%20rate%20by%202.5%25%20by%20the%20end%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20history%20has%20shown%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterest-rate-cuts-federal-reserve-economy-recession-soft-landing-powell-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed%20has%20often%20moved%20too%20late%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20reducing%20rates%2C%20Wolfenbarger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20not%20expect%20this%20time%20to%20be%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote%20in%20the%20September%209%20note.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-crash-labor-market-recession-unemployment-rate-sp500-wolfenbarger-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726304402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e47527cfb7f307e5717b7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2