icient%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20and%20accusations%20that%20federal%20agencies%20waste%20time%20and%20money%20are%20not%20always%20unwarranted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20push%20to%20make%20the%20government%20work%20more%20like%20a%20business%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcost-efficiency-isnt-best-measurement-government-policy-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emisunderstands%20a%20fundamental%20element%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20federalism%20%E2%80%94%20profit%20is%20not%20the%20end-all%2C%20be-all%2C%20political%20science%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGovernment%20is%20almost%20always%20more%20inefficient%20than%20the%20private%20sector%20because%20their%20motives%20are%20just%20different%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Christian%20Grose%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Southern%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222921%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Al%20Gore%20and%20Bill%20Clinton%20stand%20at%20a%20podium%20holding%20a%20government%20report%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e4c1eccfb7f307e57198d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221460%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20Vice%20President%20Al%20Gore%20spearheaded%20the%20Reinventing%20Government%20initiative%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20streamline%20government%20efficiency%3Cp%3ECynthia%20Johnson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227c8addd5-408c-4950-b159-3797e89f7a84%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EProfit%20vs.%20Protection%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEfforts%20to%20privatize%20parts%20of%20the%20US%20government%20date%20back%20decades.%20The%20modern-day%20push%20for%20a%20business-like%20government%20has%20its%20roots%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftheres-a-big-difference-between-reaganomics-and-trumponomics-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReaganomics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20economic%20policy%20put%20forth%20by%20President%20Ronald%20Reagan%20in%201981%2C%20which%20reduced%20regulation%2C%20slashed%20government%20spending%2C%20and%20scaled%20down%20the%20federal%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20side%20of%20the%20aisle%20took%20a%20similar%20approach%20in%201993%20when%20then-Vice%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fim-a-recovering-politician-and-wont-run-for-office-again-al-gore-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAl%20Gore%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20the%20Reinventing%20Government%20initiative%2C%20which%20attempted%20to%20streamline%20government%20processes%20and%20minimize%20bureaucracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20President%20George%20W.%20Bush%20also%20had%20a%20business%20background%2C%20making%20his%20pre-presidency%20fortune%20in%20the%20Texas%20oil%20industry.%20Once%20in%20office%2C%20Bush%20cut%20regulations%20with%20his%20Faith-Based%20and%20Community%20Initiative%2C%20which%20sought%20to%20outsource%20some%20social%20services%20to%20faith-based%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrose%20said%20the%20pro-business%20mentality%20is%20present%20in%20local%20and%20state%20government%2C%20too%2C%20adding%20that%20private%20sector%20professionals%20often%20run%20gubernatorial%20races%20on%20such%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolitical%20experts%20said%20it%20makes%20sense%20that%20business%20leaders%20like%20Musk%20would%20see%20only%20inefficiency%20and%20wastefulness%20in%20the%20government's%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20the%20motive%20is%20profit.%20The%20less%20efficient%20you%20are%2C%20the%20less%20profitable%20you%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Grose%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20inefficiency%20in%20the%20private%20sector%20isn't%20the%20same.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivitizing-public-goods-healthcare-education-doesnt-work-opinion-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment's%20job%20isn't%20to%20make%20money%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20to%20regulate%20and%20keep%20people%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20that's%20not%20efficient%20in%20an%20economic%20sense%2C%26quot%3B%20Grose%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%2C%20too%2C%20that%20the%20government%20and%20businesses%20serve%20very%20different%20stakeholders%2C%20Grose%20said.%20CEOs%20have%20to%20answer%20to%20stockholders%20and%20a%20board%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eof%20directors%20%E2%80%94%20the%20president%20has%20to%20answer%20to%20every%20American%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223300%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20and%20donald%20Trump%20sit%20at%20a%20table%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e4c276bf0250c2149367c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%20suggested%20a%20second%20Trump%20presidency%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bonce-in-a-lifetime%26quot%3B%20change%20to%20deregulate%20and%20cut%20spending.%3Cp%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2277ff06c1-a7ce-42dd-87ed-6be17fc49a6d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20pitfalls%20of%20privatized%20government%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECrouse%20said%20the%20consequences%20could%20be%20dire%20if%20Trump%20and%20Musk%20are%20able%20to%20make%20massive%20cuts%20to%20federal%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20decide%20you%20want%20to%20run%20the%20government%20entirely%20like%20a%20business%2C%20you're%20going%20to%20see%20things%20like%20poverty%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-job-market-unemployment-rising-federal-reserve-interest-rate-cut-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunemployment%3C%2Fa%3E%20increase%20because%20it%20becomes%20every%20man%20for%20himself%2C%26quot%3B%20Crouse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20of%20its%20faults%2C%20the%20federal%20government%20has%20a%20fail-safe%20of%20sorts%2C%20thanks%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20its%20massive%20size%2C%20Crouse%20said.%20She%20added%20that%20outsourcing%20critical%20government%20services%20to%20private%20companies%20runs%20the%20risk%20that%20those%20services%20could%20disappear%20if%20the%20company%20went%20bankrupt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20business%20isn't%20really%20self-correcting%2C%20at%20least%20not%20as%20easily%20as%20government%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Crouse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrouse%20said%20that%20privatizing%20the%20federal%20government%20could%20also%20lead%20to%20increased%20corruption%2C%20pointing%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprivate-prisons-lobby-for-their-own-existence-2016-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efor-profit%20prison%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20one%20example.%20In%202008%2C%20two%20Pennsylvania%20judges%20were%20convicted%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fcrime-trending-news-government-and-politics-6f30f575dc739415af1e5b47b1be50f0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccepting%20money%20in%20return%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20sending%20kids%20to%20private%20detention%20centers%20to%20increase%20occupancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBusinesses%20are%20out%20to%20make%20a%20profit%2C%20so%20they're%20going%20to%20do%20what%20they%20can%20to%20increase%20profits%2C%20and%20if%20the%20consumer%20gets%20hurt%20in%20the%20process%20of%20doing%20that%2C%20well%2C%20that's%20all%20a%20part%20of%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Crouse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20logistical%20issues%20associated%20with%20a%20business-like%20government%2C%20Grose%20said%20he%20was%20skeptical%20of%20the%20sentiment%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20Musk's%20comments%20earlier%20this%20week%2C%20casting%20doubt%20on%20whether%20a%20second%20Trump%20presidency%20would%20result%20in%20%26quot%3Bonce-in-a-lifetime%26quot%3B%20deregulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Trump%20did%20engage%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-