dge%20threw%20out%20the%20only%20defense%20offered%20in%20the%20case%3A%20a%20claim%20that%20Trump%20had%20made%20%26quot%3Bfair%20use%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20song.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20everything%20we%20asked%20for%2C%26quot%3B%20Grant%20attorney%20Brett%20Van%20Benthysen%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BOne-hundred%20percent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrant%2C%20a%20UK%20citizen%20who%20lives%20in%20Barbados%2C%20has%20been%20told%20of%20the%20decision%2C%20said%20another%20of%20his%20lawyers%2C%20Brian%20Caplan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMr.%20Grant%20believes%20that%20the%20ruling%20will%20help%20other%20artists%20and%20owners%20of%20copyrights%20defend%20against%20similar%20infringement%2C%26quot%3B%20Caplan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20complete%20victory%20for%20Plaintiffs%20as%20to%20liability.%20Plaintiffs%20will%20be%20seeking%20attorney's%20fees%20in%20the%20subsequent%20damages%20phase%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20remained%20unclear%20Friday%20night%20if%20the%20parties%20would%20agree%20to%20damages%20among%20themselves%2C%20or%20go%20to%20trial%20and%20let%20a%20jury%20pick%20a%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20either%20be%20a%20trial%20just%20on%20damages%2C%20assumedly%20before%20a%20jury%2C%20or%20we%20could%20agree%20to%20a%20number%20without%20a%20trial%2C%26quot%3B%20Van%20Benthysen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrant's%20lawsuit%20demanded%20that%20Trump%20pay%20him%20%24300%2C000%2C%20though%20that%20could%20rise%20if%20the%20former%20president%20must%20also%20pay%20the%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20in%20legal%20fees%20the%20artist%20has%20spent%20during%20four%20years%20of%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feddy-grant-electric-avenue-lyrics-explanation-donald-trump-lawyers-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEddy%20Grant%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-electric-avenue-singer-eddy-grant-depositions-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETrump%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20forced%20by%20subpoena%20to%20give%20dueling%20depositions%20in%20the%20case%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdan-scavino-subpoena-electric-avenue-singer-eddy-grant-copyright-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20former%20Trump%20adviser%20Dan%20Scavino%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20also%20deposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrant%20had%20sued%20Trump%20in%202020%2C%20over%20a%20campaign%20tweet%20%E2%80%94%20a%20crudely-drawn%2C%2055-second%20animation%20that%20showed%20then-presidential%20candidate%20Joe%20Biden%20feebly%20puttering%20along%20a%20railroad%20track%20in%20a%20push%20cart%20while%20a%20high-speed%20%26quot%3BTrump-Pence%26quot%3B%20train%20zoomed%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2040%20seconds%20of%20%26quot%3BElectric%20Avenue%26quot%3B%20plays%20as%20part%20of%20the%20soundtrack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20summarizing%20the%20history%20of%20the%20case%20in%20his%20decision%2C%20US%20District%20Judge%20John%20G.%20Koeltl%20revealed%20that%20it%20was%20Scavino%20%E2%80%94%20Trump's%20director%20of%20social%20media%20and%20deputy%20chief%20of%20staff%20for%20communications%20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20who%20uploaded%20the%20video%20to%20Trump's%20personal%20Twitter%20account%20on%20August%2012%2C%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BScavino%20testified%20that%20he%20saw%20the%20video%20on%20a%20Trump%20supporter's%20social%20media%20page%20either%20on%20the%20same%20day%20or%20the%20day%20before%20he%20posted%20the%20tweet%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BScavino%20also%20testified%20that%20he%20spoke%20with%20former%20President%20Trump%20before%20posting%20the%20tweet%20and%20that%20former%20President%20Trump%20'let%20%5Bhim%5D%20go%20with%20%5Bhis%5D%20instinct%20on%20it%20and%20post%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20video%20was%20viewed%20more%20than%2013.7%20million%20times%2C%20was%20liked%20more%20than%20350%2C000%20times%2C%20and%20was%20retweeted%20more%20than%20139%2C000%20times%2C%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrant's%20lawyers%20immediately%20sent%20Trump's%20lawyers%20a%20cease%20and%20desist%20letter%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20until%20Grant%20sued%20on%20September%201%2C%202020%20that%20the%20video%20was%20taken%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20rejecting%20Trump's%20claim%20that%20Grant%20had%20never%20properly%20secured%20a%20copyright%20for%20the%20Electric%20Avenue%20sound%20recording%2C%20the%20judge%20said%20it%20was%20enough%20that%20Grant%20held%20the%20copyright%20for%20a%20compilation%20record%20that%20included%20the%20song.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDecisions%20in%20multiple%20prior%20legal%20cases%20support%20that%20finding%2C%20the%20judge%20said.%20Trump%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20was%20unable%20to%20cite%20a%20single%20supporting%20case%2C%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20rejecting%20Trump's%20claim%20that%20the%20animation%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bfair%20use%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20song%2C%20the%20judge%20went%20methodically%20in%20his%20decision%20through%20the%20four-factor%20standard%20for%20fair-use%20exemptions%20to%20copyright.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20factor%20looks%20at%20how%20the%20copyrighted%20work%20was%20used.%20In%20Trump's%20case%2C%20Electric%20Avenue%20was%20used%20for%20a%20commercial%20purpose%2C%20not%20for%20an%20allowable%20non-profit%2C%20research%2C%20or%20educational%20purpose%2C%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20factor%20looks%20at%20whether%20the%20copyrighted%20work%20was%20%26quot%3Bcreative%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bfactual.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20clear%20that%20%26quot%3BElectric%20Avenue%20is%20a%20creative%20work%20and%20therefore%20is%20closer%20to%20the%20core%20of%20copyright%20protection%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20factor%20weighs%20how%20much%20of%20the%20copyrighted%20work%20was%20taken%20for%20an%20unauthorized%20use.%20Here%20the%20judge%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20song%20plays%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20animation%3B%20the%20excerpt%20is%20of%20central%20importance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20factor%20asks%20%26quot%3Bwhether%2C%20if%20the%20challenged%20use%20becomes%20widespread%2C%20it%20will%20adversely%20affect%20the%20potential%20market%20for%20the%20copyrighted%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20this%20case%2C%20there%20is%20no%20public%20benefit%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20defendants'%20use%20of%20'Electric%20Avenue'%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20plaintiffs%20correctly%20argue%2C%20the%20defendants%20'could%20have%20used%20any%20song%2C%20created%20a%20new%20song%2C%20or%20used%20no%20song%20at%20all%2C%20to%20convey%20the%20same%20political%20message%20in%20the%20Infringing%20video.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20damage%20to%20Grant%20could%20be%20significant%20if%20the%20copyright%20to%20his%20songs%20was%20not%20strictly%20enforced%2C%20the%20judge%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWidespread%2C%20uncompensated%20use%20of%20Grant's%20music%20in%20promotional%20videos%20%E2%80%94%20political%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%94%20would%20embolden%20would-be%20infringers%20and%20undermine%20Grant's%20ability%20to%20obtain%20compensation%20in%20exchange%20for%20licensing%20his%20music%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attorney%20for%20Trump%20did%20not%20immediately%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fembed.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25140396-grant-v-trump-summary-judgment-decision-20240913%2F%3Fembed%3D1%26responsive%3D1%26title%3D1%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Grant%20v%20Tru