22Dana%20Miranda%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63c025f933ffb700180f73f3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22466%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20Dana%20Miranda.%3Cp%3EDana%20Miranda%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EI%20grew%20up%20working%20class%20and%20learned%20good%20work%20ethic%20from%20my%20parents.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBut%20I%20didn't%20learn%20much%20else%20about%20money%2C%20because%2C%20I'm%20sure%2C%20my%20parents%20were%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20financial%20services.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWorking%20for%20a%20personal%20finance%20startup%20opened%20my%20eyes%20to%20the%20ways%20I%20could%20use%20money%20to%20thrive.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20about%208%20or%209%20years%20old%2C%20my%20parents%20offered%20my%20sister%20and%20me%20our%20first%20allowance.%20We%20were%20each%20responsible%20for%20a%20rotating%20set%20of%20weekly%20chores%2C%20and%20we%20each%20got%20%243%20a%20week%20for%20completing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20was%2010%20or%2011%2C%20they%20discontinued%20the%20allowance%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20parents%20realized%20using%20money%20as%20an%20incentive%20meant%20we%20could%20forfeit%20the%20week's%20pay%20if%20we%20didn't%20want%20to%20do%20the%20housework%20on%20our%20list.%20We%20were%20elementary%20school%20children%20with%20parents%20to%20feed%2C%20clothe%2C%20and%20house%20us%2C%20so%20we%20had%20little%20need%20for%20money.%20The%20novelty%20of%20cap%20erasers%20and%20Airheads%20from%20the%20school%20store%20wore%20off%20fast%2C%20and%20money%20didn't%20have%20much%20luster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20housework%20still%20needed%20to%20get%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20they%20pulled%20the%20allowance%20and%20instituted%20a%20%26quot%3BYou%20do%20the%20chores%20because%20we%20told%20you%20to%20do%20the%20chores%26quot%3B%20policy%20in%20its%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20earliest%20I%20remember%20learning%20anything%20about%20money%20from%20my%20parents.%20The%20lesson%3F%20You%20do%20work%20because%20work%20needs%20to%20be%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20a%20rural%2C%20working-class%20family%20from%20the%20Midwest.%20In%20our%20part%20of%20Wisconsin%2C%20with%20its%20German%20roots%20and%20farm%20families%2C%20work%20ethic%20is%20our%20moral%20code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20didn't%20teach%20us%20much%20about%20our%20country's%20financial%20systems%20%E2%80%94%20because%2C%20I%20assume%2C%20they%20were%20as%20much%20in%20the%20dark%20about%20them%20as%20most%20Americans%20are.%20We%20didn't%20talk%20about%20financial%20services%2C%20because%20they%20aren't%20built%20for%20people%20like%20us%2C%20who%20are%2C%20as%20my%20parents%20put%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20born%20rich.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20taught%20us%20how%20to%20work%2C%20and%20that%20shaped%20everything%20I%20believed%20about%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20'good%20work%20ethic'%20means%20for%20your%20finances%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it's%20in%20my%20DNA%2C%20I%20can't%20help%20but%20see%20a%20strong%20work%20ethic%20as%20a%20virtue.%20My%20efficiency%2C%20stoicism%2C%20and%20persistence%20have%20earned%20me%20the%20life%20my%20parents%20hoped%20I'd%20have%20%E2%80%94%20one%20where%20I%20earn%20double%20what%20they%20did%20at%20my%20age%20and%20have%20the%20adventures%20they%20delayed%20to%20raise%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20glorification%20of%20work%20ethic%20is%20insidious.%20It%20underpins%20millennial%20hustle%20culture%20and%20the%20ridiculous%20politics%20that%20have%20stuck%20us%20with%20a%20federal%20minimum%20wage%20that%20hasn't%20budged%20in%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20do%20the%20work%20because%20it%20needs%20to%20get%20done%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20attitude%20that%20kept%20my%20mom%20silent%20when%20she%20knew%20she%20earned%20less%20money%20than%20her%20male%20coworkers%20while%20doing%20more%20work%20and%20honing%20more%20skills%20to%20stand%20out.%20It%20motivated%20my%20stepdad%20to%20be%20promoted%20to%20supervisor%20in%20his%20manufacturing%20job%2C%20only%20to%20lose%20all%20the%20protections%20of%20his%20union%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20turn%20his%20bitterness%20on%20the%20union%20workers%20instead%20of%20the%20system%20that%20pit%20him%20against%20them.%20It%20convinced%20my%20dad%20not%20to%20chase%20down%20payments%20owed%20for%20his%20construction%20jobs%2C%20even%20when%20his%20electricity%20was%20being%20cut%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOperating%20on%20work%20ethic%20means%20you%20make%20do%20with%20what%20you%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20money%20management%20a%20matter%20of%20discipline.%20You%20don't%20expect%20more%2C%20you%20don't%20spend%20more%20than%20you%20make%2C%20and%20you%20never%20ask%20for%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20we're%20white%20and%20able-bodied%2C%20we%20were%20inherently%20trained%20to%20believe%20paying%20work%20would%20be%20available%20as%20long%20as%20we%20were%20willing%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBuild%20a%20budget%20that%20works%20for%20you%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fbest-budgeting-apps%5C%22%3Ebest%20budgeting%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20help%20you%20get%20your%20finances%20in%20order%20and%20track%20your%20monthly%20spending.%20Top%20offers%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Frocket-money-app-review%5C%22%3ERocket%20Money%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbanking%2Fsimplifi-by-quicken-review%5C%22%3ESimplifi%20by%20Quicken%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Ch2%3EOvercoming%20internalized%20budget%20culture%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents'%20disciplined%20approach%20to%20money%20is%20pretty%20much%20in%20line%20with%20the%20maxims%20of%20overall%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20hr