0human%20resources%2C%20it%20requires%20hard%20work%2C%20until%20you%20build%20the%20infrastructure%2C%20until%20you%20have%20those%20policies.%20So%20life%20is%20not%20%3Cem%3E'khata-khat%3C%2Fem%3E'.%20Life%20is%20hard%20work.%20Life%20is%20diligence.%20Anybody%20who's%20held%20a%20job%20and%20laboured%20at%20it%2C%20knows%20it.%20So%20that's%20my%20message%20to%20you%2C%20that%20we%20have%20to%20work%20hard%20at%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20a%20country%20cannot%20be%20a%20major%20power%20in%20the%20world%20without%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20there%20are...people%20who%20say%20that%20we%20are%20incapable%20of%20it%2C%20we%20should%20not%20even%20attempt%20it.%20So%2C%20now%20ask%20yourself%2C%20can%20you%20actually%20be%20a%20major%20power%20in%20the%20world%20without%20manufacturing%3F%20Because%20a%20major%20power%20needs%20technology.%20Nobody%20can%20develop%20technology%20without%20developing%20manufacturing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FWATCH%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23WATCH%3C%2Fa%3E%20%7C%20Interacting%20with%20the%20Indian%20community%20in%20Geneva%2C%20EAM%20Dr%20S%20Jaishankar%20says%2C%20%26quot%3B...Until%20you%20build%20infrastructure%20%26amp%3B%20human%20resources%2C%20have%20those%20policies%20in%20place%2C%20it%20is%20hard%20work.%20Life%20is%20not%20'khata-khat'%2C%20life%20is%20hard%20work%20and%20diligence...%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn(Video%20source%3A%20Ministry%20of%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FBdcv76dNgJ%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FBdcv76dNgJ%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20ANI%20(%40ANI)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FANI%2Fstatus%2F1834556740303802429%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%2013%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20in%20terms%20of%20human%20resources%2C%20India%20has%20achieved%20a%20lot%20and%20the%20intent%20today%20is%20to%20ramp%20it%20up%20even%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20terms%20of%20human%20resources...%20it's%20again%20important%20to%20look%20here%20at%20achievements.%20So%20I%20can%20tell%20you%20the%20intent%20today%20is%20actually%20to%20speed%20it%20up%2C%20to%20ramp%20it%20up%2C%20to%20increase%20it%2C%20to%20keep%20telling%20ourselves%20that%20what%20we%20have%20done%20is%20just%20a%20beginning.%20I%20mean%20there%20is%20no%20intention%20of%20resting%20on%20whatever%20levels%20there%20may%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20apart%20from%20the%20professional%20conversation%2C%20world%20leaders%20are%20interested%20in%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20travel%20around%20the%20world-%20and%20you%20would%20have%20noticed%20I%20do%20a%20fair%20deal%20of%20that%20%5Bchuckles%5D-%20most%20of%20my%20counterparts%2C%20most%20of%20the%20presidents%20and%20prime%20ministers%20are%20meet.%20Yes%2C%20we%20do%20the%20foreign%20policy%2C%20but%20that's%20the%20professional%20part%20of%20it.%20But%20they%20are%20enormously%20interested%2C%20actually%2C%20in%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20the%20conversation%2C%20even%20the%20words%2C%20are%20very%20similar.%20I%20had%20the%20leader%20of%20a%20very%20major%20Arab%20country%20actually%20say%2C%20we%20have%20food%20distribution%20system%20and%2C%20Minister%2C%20you%20don't%20know%20how%20much%20leakage%20we%20have.%20Because%20he%20was%20very%20interested%2C%20how%20do%20we%20today%20manage%20the%20food%20support%2C%20where%20today%20they%20are%20covering%20830%20million%20people.%20How%20do%20we%20manage%20that%20with%20actually%20much%20less%20leakage%20than%20there%20has%20ever%20been%20in%20the%20past%3F%20People%20who%20ask%20today%2C%20how%20have%20you%20improved%20your%20income%20tax%20collection%3F%20Because%20every%20president%20and%20prime%20minister%20is%20interested%20in%20increasing%20their%20revenues%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaishankar%20added%2C%20talking%20about%20food%20support%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20said%20that%20in%20what%20India%20is%20doing%2C%20there%20are%20lessons%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20look%20back%20at%20these%20ten%20years%2C%20yes%2C%20there%20have%20been%20changes%20for%20the%20good%20in%20our%20country%2C%20but%20I%20will%20also%20say%20to%20all%20of%20you%20that%20those%20changes%20actually%20globally%20resonate.%20That%20other%20countries%20today%20look%20with%20deep%20interest%2C%20they%20may%20not%20be%20able%20to%20exactly%20copy%20it%2C%20but%20somewhere%20in%20what%20we%20are%20doing%20there%20are%20lessons%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20And%20people%20feel%20this%20country%2C%20which%2C%20bear%20in%20mind%2C%20which%20still%20has%20USD%203000%20per%20capita%20income%20below%20that%2C%20is%20able%20to%20do%20that%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Jaishankar%20added%20that%20achievements%20are%20meant%20to%20motivate%20and%20not%20be%20satiated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAchievements%20not%20to%20satiate%20but%20to%20motivate.%20Not%20to%20say%20I've%20done%20well%2C%20so%20I'm%20done.%20But%20to%20say%20I've%20done%20well%20and%20I%20could%20have%20done%20so%20much%20more.%20And%20if%20I%20could%20have%20done%20this%20in%20two%20terms%2C%20how%20much%20more%20can%20I%20do%20in%20a%20third%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726238400000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F1ht0ulco_s-jaishankar_625x300_13_September_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flife-is-not-khata-khat-it-is-hardwork-s-jaishankars-swipe-at-rahul-gandhi-6558408%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22External%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20while%20addressing%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%20in%20Geneva%20said%20that%20life%20is%20not%20%26quot%3Bkhata-khat%26quot%3B%20(an%20easy%20job)%2C%20it%20requires%20hard%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Flife-is-not-khata-khat-it-is-hardwork-s-jaishankars-swipe-at-rahul-gandhi-6558408%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Groundwater%20in%20Leh%20Will%20Suffer%20Rapid%20Decline%20in%2020-30%20Years%3A%20What%20Can%20the%20City%20Do%20To%20Fix%20It%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20Choglamsar%2C%20a%20dusty%20urban%20settlement%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Leh%20town%2C%20Dr%20Lobzang%20Chorol%20witnessed%20firsthand%20the%20critical%20role%20water%20plays%20in%20this%20cold%20desert.%20Speaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Dr%20Chorol%20recalls%20two%20specific%20incidents%20that%20left%20an%20indelible%20impression%20on%20her.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDuring%20my%20childhood%2C%20I%20vividly%20remember%20a%20summer%20when%20the%20PHE%20(Public%20Health%20and%20Engineering)%20tanker%20failed%20to%20arrive%2C%20leaving%20us%20without%20a%20water%20supply.%20We%20had%20to%20walk%20long%20distances%20to%20fetch%20water%20for%20our%20basic%20needs.%20I%20saw%20the%20worry%20on%20my%20parent%E2%80%99s%20faces%20and%20the%20strain%20it%20put%20on%20our%20entire%20community.%20This%20crisis%20opened%20my%20eyes%20to%20the%20fragility%20of%20our%20water%20resources%20and%20the%20urgent%20need%20for%20better%20management%20and%20understanding%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20incident%20Dr%20Chorol%20recalls%20is%20from%20her%20undergraduate%20days%20when%20she%20visited%20her%20ancestral%20village%20called%20Skumpata%20(Lingshet)%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F302635%2Fladakh-ministry-of-education-score-new-heights-role-of-dedicated-teachers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELadakh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20about%2080%20km%20from%20Leh%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20struck%20by%20the%20ingenious%20traditional%20water%20management%20systems%20our%20ancestors%20had%20developed%20%E2%80%94%20the%20intricate%20network%20of%20channels%20and%20storage%20ponds%20that%20had%20sustained%20life%20in%20this%20harsh%20landscape%20for%20centuries.%20However%2C%20I%20also%20noticed%20how%20these%20systems%20were%20under%20threat%20from%20changing%20climate%20patterns%20and%20modernisation.%20It%20made%20me%20realise%20the%20importance%20of%20bridging%20traditional%20knowledge%20with%20modern%20scientific%20approaches%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FIMG_20230423_110238_478-1726233445-500x625.webp%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20Lobzang%20Chorol%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FIMG_20230423_110238_478-1726233445-500x625.webp%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FIMG_20230423_110238_478-1726233445-240x300.webp%20240w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FIMG_20230423_110238_478-1726233445-150x188.webp%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FIMG_20230423_110238_478-1726233445.webp%20736w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365885%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22625%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EDr%20Lobzang%20Chorol%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20this%20fascination%20and%20concern%20that%20motivated%20her%20to%20better%20understand%20the%20cold%20desert%E2%80%99s%20water%20systems%20to%20pursue%20her%20PhD%20at%20IIT-ISM%20(Indian%20School%20of%20Mines)%2C%20Dhanbad.%20Under%20the%20mentorship%20of%20Professor%20Sunil%20Kumar%20Gupta%2C%20a%20leading%20expert%20in%20the%20field%2C%20she%20closely%20studied%20the%20groundwater%20systems%20in%20Leh%20town.%20Spanning%20six%20years%20and%20eight%20months%2C%20her%20research%20finally%20culminated%20in%20the%20completion%20of%20her%20thesis%20earlier%20this%20year.%20(You%20can%20find%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fprofile%2FLobzang-Chorol%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20times%20when%20the%20challenges%20seemed%20overwhelming%20%E2%80%94%20from%20people%20unwilling%20to%20give%20their%20borewell%20water%20samples%20to%20collecting%20secondary%20baseline%20data%20and%20the%20emotional%20weight%20of%20seeing%20the%20deterioration%20of%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20water%20resources%20firsthand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20every%20time%20I%20felt%20discouraged%2C%20I%20remembered%20the%20faces%20of%20my%20family%20and%20community%20back%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20depending%20on%20this%20precious%20resource.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20academic%20research%3B%20it%20was%20about%20the%20lives%20and%20futures%20of%20real%20people.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20about%20earning%20a%20degree%3B%20it%20was%20about%20securing%20a%20sustainable%20future%20for%20Ladakh%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELeh%E2%80%99s%20invisible%20network%20of%20underground%20aquifers%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeh%20is%20a%20town%20nestled%20in%20the%20rain%20shadow%20area%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F312359%2Fscientist-innovates-solar-hamam-warm-water-heater-for-thousands-in-himachal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emighty%20Himalayas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20receiving%20barely%20100%20mm%20of%20annual%20rainfall.%20Life%20in%20this%20high-altitude%20desert%20thrives%20against%20all%20odds%2C%20thanks%20to%20an%20invisible%20network%20of%20underground%20aquifers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20aquifers%20are%20essentially%20natural%20underground%20reservoirs%20formed%20in%20the%20porous%20layers%20of%20rock%20and%20sediment%20beneath%20Leh.%20They%20are%20recharged%20primarily%20by%20snowmelt%20from%20surrounding%20mountains%2C%20glacial%20melt%20from%20nearby%20glaciers%2C%20limited%20annual%20rainfall%2C%20and%20infiltration%20from%20rivers%20and%20streams.%20This%20recharge%20process%20is%20heavily%20influenced%20by%20seasonal%20patterns%2C%20with%20most%20occurring%20during%20the%20warmer%20months%20when%20snow%20and%20glaciers%20melt%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20aquifers%20act%20as%20a%20natural%20storage%20and%20filtration%20system%2C%20holding%20water%20that%20percolates%20through%20the%20ground%20and%20releasing%20it%20slowly%20over%20time.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20groundwater%20maintains%20a%20relatively%20stable%20temperature%2C%20which%20can%20be%20beneficial%20for%20both%20ecosystems%20and%20human%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20920px)%20100vw%2C%20920px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leh's%20groundwater%20gets%20recharged%20by%20snowmelt%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591.jpg%20920w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-300x161.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-500x268.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-768x412.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-groundwater-1-1726233591-150x81.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365887%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22494%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELeh%E2%80%99s%20underground%20network%20of%20aquifers%20is%20recharged%20by%20snowmelt%20and%20glacial%20melt.%20(Image%20courtesy%3A%20Reach%20Ladakh)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20way%20these%20aquifers%20support%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20thriving%20is%20multifaceted.%20They%20sustain%20natural%20vegetation%20crucial%20for%20the%20local%20ecosystem%20and%20enable%20agriculture%20in%20an%20otherwise%20arid%20environment.%20For%20human%20use%2C%20they%20feed%20springs%20used%20for%20drinking%20water%2C%20supply%20water%20for%20wells%2C%20and%20support%20traditional%20water%20management%20systems%20like%20%3Cem%3Ezings%3C%2Fem%3E%20(ponds)%20and%20%3Cem%3Eyura%3C%2Fem%3E%20(channels)%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20stored%20water%20in%20aquifers%20helps%20Leh%20withstand%20periods%20of%20low%20precipitation%2C%20providing%20resilience%20against%20drought.%20This%20consistent%20water%20supply%20allows%20for%20urban%20development%20and%20supports%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F282723%2Fbest-homestays-in-ladakh-things-to-do-in-leh-local-experience%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrowing%20tourism%20%3C%2Fa%3Eindustry%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20and%20properly%20managing%20this%20invisible%20network%20of%20aquifers%20is%20crucial%20for%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20sustainable%20future%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20face%20of%20climate%20change%20and%20increasing%20water%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20crucial%20lifeline%20is%20under%20severe%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Slowly%20poisoning%20the%20very%20veins%20that%20sustain%20us%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20rising%20tourist%20footfall%2C%20unplanned%20development%20and%20poor%20water%20management%20practices%2C%20Dr%20Chorol%E2%80%99s%20nearly%20seven-year%20research%20into%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20groundwater%20has%20come%20up%20with%20some%20troubling%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDecline%20in%20water%20quality%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%9COver%20the%20past%20six%20years%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20observed%20a%20significant%20decrease%20in%20water%20quality.%20For%20instance%2C%20Total%20Dissolved%20Solids%20(TDS)%20levels%20have%20increased%20by%20about%2030%25%20in%20some%20areas%2C%20from%20an%20average%20of%20300%20mg%2FL%20to%20over%20400%20mg%2FL.%20This%20rapid%20increase%20is%20alarming.%20To%20give%20you%20an%20idea%20of%20how%20serious%20the%20problem%20is%2C%20let%20me%20share%20some%20of%20our%20key%20findings%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20drinking%20water%2C%20we%20found%20that%203.57%25%20of%20our%20samples%20were%20of%20extremely%20poor%20quality%2C%20and%20another%203.57%25%20were%20poor.%20What%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20concerning%20is%20that%2092.86%25%20were%20only%20of%20average%20quality%2C%20and%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20find%20any%20samples%20in%20the%20good%20or%20excellent%20categories%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNitrate%20levels%20have%20risen%20by%20up%20to%2050%25%20in%20certain%20wells%2C%20approaching%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20(WHO)%20limit%20of%2050%20mg%2FL%20in%20some%20cases.%20We%E2%80%99ve%20also%20detected%20increasing%20concentrations%20of%20heavy%20metals%20like%20chromium%20and%20cadmium%20with%20some%20samples%20showing%20levels%20two%20to%20three%20times%20higher%20than%20what%20we%20observed%20six%20years%20ago.%20For%20irrigation%20water%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20equally%20worrying.%20We%20found%20that%203.57%25%20of%20samples%20were%20very%20poor%2C%2042.86%25%20were%20poor%2C%20and%2053.57%25%20were%20average.%20This%20indicates%20a%20widespread%20issue%20with%20water%20quality%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChange%20in%20groundwater%20chemistry%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20chemical%20composition%20of%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20groundwater%20has%20altered%20noticeably.%20%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20increased%20levels%20of%20ions%20like%20chloride%2C%20sulphate%2C%20and%20sodium%2C%20which%20are%20typically%20associated%20with%20human%20activities.%20For%20example%2C%20chloride%20concentrations%20have%20risen%20by%20about%2040%25%20in%20some%20wells%20over%20the%20six%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20change%20suggests%20contamination%20from%20sources%20like%20improper%20sewage%20disposal%20and%20the%20concentration%20of%20major%20cations%20has%20increased%2C%20following%20the%20order%20of%20calcium%2C%20magnesium%2C%20sodium%2C%20and%20potassium.%20We%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20higher%20levels%20of%20sodium%2C%20potassium%2C%20fluoride%2C%20and%20nitrates%2C%20which%20we%20believe%20are%20linked%20to%20the%20increased%20use%20of%20agrochemicals%20in%20agriculture%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20particularly%20concerning%20is%20the%20elevated%20levels%20of%20heavy%20metals%20we%E2%80%99re%20detecting.%20Iron%2C%20manganese%2C%20chromium%2C%20nickel%2C%20cadmium%2C%20and%20copper%20are%20all%20present%20at%20levels%20exceeding%20permissible%20limits%20in%20many%20of%20the%20samples%20studied%20by%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99re%20seeing%20contamination%20from%20various%20sources%20%E2%80%94%20sewage%20leaking%20from%20poorly%20maintained%20septic%20systems%2C%20agricultural%20runoff%20from%20fertilisers%2C%20waste%20from%20increased%20tourism%2C%20and%20lack%20of%20proper%20wastewater%20treatment%20facilities.%20Each%20of%20these%20sources%20might%20seem%20small%20on%20its%20own%20but%20together%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20having%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20our%20water%20quality.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20complex%20issue%2C%20but%20understanding%20it%20is%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20addressing%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leh%20groundwater%20is%20suffering%20due%20to%20poor%20sewage%20management%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F09%2FLeh-Groundwater-Image-5-1726233757-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-365888%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EA%20sewer%20cleaning%20truck%20in%20Leh%3A%20Sewage%20management%20is%20a%20serious%20problem%20in%20this%20high-altitude%20town%20(Image%20courtesy%20Shutterstock%2F%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shutterstock.com%2Fg%2FOliverFoerstner%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOliver%20Foerstner%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHealth%20risks%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%9CFirstly%2C%20we%20found%20that%20certain%20heavy%20metals%2C%20such%20as%20chromium%2C%20cadmium%2C%20and%20nickel%2C%20present%20in%20the%20groundwater%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20increase%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F349895%2Fhow-to-deal-with-cancer-diagnosis-regular-health-checkup-turbt-battle-india-chemo-therapy-ninad-raikar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erisk%20of%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20risk%20is%20particularly%20concerning%20for%20children%2C%20who%20are%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20effects%20of%20these%20contaminants%20due%20to%20their%20developing%20bodies%20and%20higher%20water%20intake%20relative%20to%20their%20body%20weight.%20In%20addition%20to%20the%20carcinogenic%20risk%2C%20we%20also%20identified%20non-carcinogenic%20health%20risks%20posed%20by%20chromium%20in%20the%20groundwater%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Dr%20Chorol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20heavy%20metals%2C%20her%20study%20also%20investigated%20the%20health%20risks%20associated%20with%20fluoride%20and%20nitrate%20exposure%20in%20the%20groundwater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20hazard%20quotient%20analysis%20revealed%20that%20the%20oral%20pathway%2C%20i.e.%20drinking%20contaminated%20water%2C%20was%20the%20primary%20route%20of%20exposure%20for%20all%20age%20groups.%20Fluoride%20and%20nitrate%20were%20found%20to%20be%20the%20major%20contributors%20to%20these%20health%20risks%20with%20children%20and%20infants%20being%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20to%20their%20effects.%20Fluoride%2C%20when%20consumed%20in%20excess%2C%20can%20lead%20to%20dental%20and%20skeletal%20fluorosis%2C%20which%20can%20cause%20discolouration%20and%20damage%20to%20the%20teeth%20and%20bones.%20Nitrate%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20can%20interfere%20with%20t